  "doc_id": "24294",
  "text": "Power calculation was carried out a priori on the primary outcome (ie, insulin sensitivity) based on previous data on healthy prepubertal children obtained via an identical FSIGT protocol [CITATION_1] . This gave a sample size of 36 participants to detect an insulin sensitivity index difference of 3.6 ϫ 10 Ϫ4 ⅐min Ϫ1 ⅐(mU/L) between 2 groups (approximately 30%) with 90% power at 5% level of significance, assuming a SD of 4.4 ϫ 10 Ϫ4 ⅐min Ϫ1 ⅐(mU/L).",
  "correct_citation": {
